{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599208","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599208"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:50:16+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:50:16+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15533"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15533","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15533"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8224"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67648"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8224","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8224"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15533"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53100"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7005"},{"type":"tags","id":"7009"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19887"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19891"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22664"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67648","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67648"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe arterial supply to the superior and inferior parathyroid glands is via one main vessel.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following arteries provides the main blood supply to the parathyroid glands?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Ascending cervical artery","Inferior thyroid artery","Superior laryngeal artery","Superior thyroid artery","Thyroidea ima artery"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Einferior thyroid artery\u003C/strong\u003E is the main blood supply to both the superior and inferior parathyroid glands. This artery is a branch of the thyrocervical trunk, which originates from the subclavian artery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperior thyroid artery\u003C/strong\u003E primarily supplies the upper pole of the thyroid gland. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ethyroidea ima artery\u003C/strong\u003E, when present, supplies the lower portion of the thyroid gland. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eascending cervical artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the deep muscles of the neck. The \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperior laryngeal artery\u003C/strong\u003E supplies the larynx and its associated structures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the blood supply to the parathyroid glands is crucial during thyroid surgery to prevent inadvertent damage to these glands, which could result in hypoparathyroidism.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The inferior thyroid artery is the main blood supply to the parathyroid glands","The parathyroid glands are typically located on the posterior surface of the thyroid gland"],"references":["Sadowski SM, Vidal Fortuny J, Triponez F. A reappraisal of vascular anatomy of the parathyroid gland based on fluorescence techniques. Gland Surg. 2017 Dec;6(Suppl 1):S30-S37. doi: 10.21037/gs.2017.07.10. PMID: 29322020; PMCID: PMC5756753.","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd.","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53100"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15533"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53100","links":{"self":"https: